scene.message:
Brown: Don't they sell any{nl}
super-powerful guns or armor?{nl}
Will we be okay with such{nl}
flimsy gear?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Open for business even{nl}
with demons about — quite{nl}
admirable.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: I wonder if the demons{nl}
won't come inside the store.{nl}
Either way, it's a relief.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: It's a strange feeling.{nl}
Being here, I start to wonder{nl}
if all of it was just{nl}
a dream.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Hey, what're we gonna{nl}
do about SEBEC? Are we done{nl}
with it already~?{waitkey}{ret}

Clerk: ...{wait_fr:16}Even demons won't{nl}
come inside the store, right?{wait_fr:21}{nl}
I've got to keep it open...{waitkey}{clearbox}We're open year-round, after{nl}
all...{wait_fr:32} Welcome!{waitkey}{ret}
